PN,30609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1783792086
OL,3,CFormer news presenter Dermot Murnaghan
OL,4,Chas died aged 68
OL,6,FIn 2007, Dermot Murnaghan became one
OL,7,Fof the lead anchors on Sky News,
OL,8,Fbeginning 16 years with the channel.
OL,10,FHis Sunday Morning political programme
OL,11,Fsaw him interview some of the biggest
OL,12,Fnames in Westminster. On both sides of
OL,13,Fthe Atlantic, he covered successive
OL,14,Felections for the channel. In
OL,15,FSeptember 2022, it was his voice
OL,16,Fentrusted with anchoring special
OL,17,Fcoverage from Buckingham Palace.
OL,19,FAs a presenter over many years, Dermot
OL,20,FMurnaghan came into millions of homes
OL,21,Fwith news of major events.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
